 [FILE PHOTO] Osun state  While 14 were crushed to death by a truck carrying flammable content around a power line along Ipetu-Ijesa/Ilesa way on Saturday evening, two  persons died in a lone car accident that occurred around Niger Cat Area after Babalakin Hall, Gbongan-Osogbo highway, Gbongan on Sunday. The crash involving 14 persons happened around 5:40 p.m. when a truck collided with a Sienna car. Spokesperson for the Osun Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Command, Agnes Ogungbemi, said the victims included six children while two people survived. The vehicles involved are Toyota Sienna with registration number KRD842GY and  Howo Sinotruck with registration number BAU171ZE. “Four males, four females, and six children while two male adults sustained injuries. The mutilated corpses were taken to Wesley Hospital morgue, Ilesa,” she said. Also, one male and one female, both unidentified, died while five others sustained injuries in a crash around 1:35 p.m. on Sunday. The accident involved one Toyota Previa minibus, colour wine with registration number GNN57XD. She said that the injured were taken by sympathisers to Iseoluwa Hospital, Ode Omu before the arrival of the FRSC team while two other victims were taken to Ariremako Hospital, Gbongan. “The corpses were deposited at OAUTH morgue, Ile-Ife,” she said.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .